text.text:
So hotel palm galaxy has been built atop the rashtradeep restaurant, an old and famous dhaba which has evolved into a fine restaurant. It has decent, clean rooms which can be used for short business/couple/family trips. Food can be a limitation here though, since Zomato and swiggy are not available and the restaurant serves mainly Desi Indian food.

The service is decent, I had a minor electricity issue which took time to fix but the staff was apologetic about it so that's good.

Overall though, it offers good value for the cost they charge and I'd be okay with a second stay here if the need so arises.

text.text: Parivaar hotel is approximately 2 km from railway station. I have visited tundla many times but this hotel for accomodation for the first time. This is perfect for budget accommodation and short stay. Very reasonable in cost around Rs 800 per night. They also have restaurant which serves normal food and nothing fancy. text.text: Stayed in the hotel and ate at the restaurant. Food was well-made and tasty, though service was quite slow (it took 30 minutes to make us coffee, and the restaurant had almost nobody else in it). Servers were friendly. Room was okay. There was a tv, AC, fans, a balcony with a nice view of the street, a big bed (bring your own sheets/blankets), and a bathroom. The bathroom had a Western-style toilet, a sink, and a shower (which was essentially just a pipe that shot one stream of water out of the wall). Overall, this was what I expected from a hotel in a small town in India.

text.text: Stayed in hotel in the last fortnight for 2 days.rate for ac room quoted as 1200₹ non ac room ₹800.on persuasion came down to 1000 & 600 respectively.i opted for non ac.room etc was ok.there was a TV,geyser  .a restaurant also which are a rare sight in tundla.but restaurant ok for family get-together but not for an individual as it works out costly.generally ate at a close-by dhaba type jt.quite reasonable with dal,roti,chawal.bagal maine beer/wine shop as well for those interested in it.bagal maine Jio mobile,clothes,general merchants store+a local delicacy bedai(stuffed kachori/jalebi/dahi/chai shop .very easily accessible to rly.station.auto raat bhar chalti hain.i had to take a morning 4 o'clock train.wondering whether would get conveance but got it within 5 mts.hotel needs maintenance but in a tundla type down town it is a good place to sleepover and rest.no doubt rates were further negotiable but I didn't bargain further as I found it a good proposition for passing of my time.
